        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Ghrelin is the ligand for growth hormone secretagogue receptor type 1 (GHSR). Induces the release of growth hormone from the pituitary. Has an appetite-stimulating effect, induces adiposity and stimulates gastric acid secretion. Involved in growth regulation"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Obestatin may be the ligand for GPR39. May have an appetite-reducing effect resulting in decreased food intake. May reduce gastric emptying activity and jejunal motility"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SUBCELLULAR LOCATION",
          "subcellularLocations": [
